as man Peter Minshall, and resilient HIV/AIDS organization Friends For Life. Erotic Islands traverses black studies, queer studies, and anthropology toward an emergent black queer diaspora studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAIDS activistszTrinidad and Tobago. 0aBlack peoplezTrinidad and Tobago. 0aCalypso (Music)xSocial aspectszTrinidad and Tobago. 0aCarnivalxSocial aspectszTrinidad and Tobago. 0aGays in popular culturezTrinidad and Tobago. 0aGayszTrinidad and Tobago. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aLAMMY finalist.  aLambda Literary Awards.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106963320 cprintz978082236858840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822372622423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780822372622/original  a978-3-11-069633-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles